$ gcc -Wp

`gcc -Wp`: pass options to the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/CPP/preprocessor[preprocessor].

{ prog.c

  The following program uses → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc#printf-family[`printf`], yet wihtout including `stdio.h`. Additionally, the macro `FOO` is not defined in the translation unit:
  gh|about-gcc|/options/Wp/prog.c||

}
{ Makefile

  When the following makefile invokes `gcc`, it uses the `-Wp` option to pass the `-D` and `-include` options to the preprocessor so that `FOO` is defined and `stdio.h` included.

  gh|about-gcc|/options/Wp/Makefile||

}
